# CODEOWNERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Defines who is automatically requested for review when PRs touch these paths.
# Syntax: <pattern> <owner> [<owner> ...]
#
# Rules are matched top-to-bottom; the LAST matching rule wins for a given path.
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ── Global fallback ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Every file requires review unless a more specific rule below also matches.
*                                   @jourlez

# ── CI/CD workflows ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Workflow changes can exfiltrate secrets or silently disable security gates.
.github/                            @jourlez
.github/workflows/                  @jourlez

# ── Workspace-wide tooling ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Changes here affect every package in the monorepo.
nx.json                             @jourlez
pnpm-workspace.yaml                 @jourlez
package.json                        @jourlez
tsconfig.base.json                  @jourlez
biome.json                          @jourlez
lefthook.yml                        @jourlez
knip.json                           @jourlez
renovate.json                       @jourlez
vitest.base.config.ts               @jourlez

# ── Module boundary enforcement ───────────────────────────────────────────────
scripts/                            @jourlez
tools/                              @jourlez

# ── Container definitions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dockerfile changes affect the production attack surface and supply chain.
**/Dockerfile                       @jourlez
**/Dockerfile.*                     @jourlez

# ── Cryptographic packages ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Subtle changes here can introduce vulnerabilities without obvious build failures.
packages/jvm/blst/                  @jourlez
packages/jvm/curve25519/            @jourlez
packages/jvm/groth16/               @jourlez
packages/sdk/crypto/                @jourlez

# ── SDK public API surface ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Breaking changes affect downstream consumers — external integrators and all apps.
packages/sdk/                       @jourlez
packages/ride/                      @jourlez

# ── Security policy ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECURITY.md                         @jourlez
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md                  @jourlez
